Author-Name:    Ehrlich, Isaac
Author-Name:  Lui, Francis T
Title:   Intergenerational Trade, Longevity, and Economic Growth. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 1029-59
Issue: 5
Volume: 99
Year: 1991
Month:  October 
Abstract:
  The authors develop an overlapping-generations model of endogenous growth
 in which human capital is the engine of growth and the generations are
 linked through material and emotional interdependencies within the family.
 Parents invest in their children to achieve both old-age support (care)
 and emotional gratification, and material support from children is
 determined through self-enforcing implicit contracts. The authors show
 that optimal intergenerational trade can then lead to maximization of
 growth opportunities. Their model produces a theory of the "demographic
 transition" linking longevity, fertility, and economic growth.  Copyright 1991 by University of Chicago Press.
