Author-Name:    Bernheim, B Douglas
Title:   How Strong Are Bequest Motives? Evidence Based on Estimates of the Demand for Life Insurance and Annuities. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 899-927
Issue: 5
Volume: 99
Year: 1991
Month:  October 
Abstract:
  This paper presents new empirical evidence in support of the view that a
 significant fraction of total saving is motivated by the desire to leave
 bequests. Specifically, the author finds that social security annuity
 benefits significantly raise life insurance holdings and depress private
 annuity holdings among elderly individuals. These patterns indicate that
 the typical household would choose to maintain a positive fraction of its
 resources in bequeathable forms, even if insurance markets were perfect.
 Evidence on the relationship between insurance purchases and total
 resources reinforces this conclusion.  Copyright 1991 by University of Chicago Press.
